						               													<description>Can you find the treasure in trash?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Under the tyranny of the wealthy, JunkLand has become the world&amp;rsquo;s garbage dump. This once pristine land has been reduced to a stinky landfill. But for the Lords of JunkLand this place is a goldmine. There are treasures in the trash that help them earn a living and keep the world safe and clean. They are the unsung heroes of humanity!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Lord of the Bins is a strategy card game that tests players&amp;rsquo; knowledge about segregating trash and your ability to outwit opponents. It involves elements of hand management, placement, trick taking and push-your-luck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to Play?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Segregate the waste in the Trash Cards and put them in the 4 bins - dry waste, wet waste, e-waste and hazardous &amp;amp; sanitary waste. Remember to put them in the correct bin and collect treasure to play special powers!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Trash Marketplace - Players first collect Trash Cards from the marketplace. You can choose what to collect, but you place gems on what you skip! When you pick cards, collect gems too!&amp;#10;     Take Out The Trash! - Once you've picked cards from the marketplace, then you can drop them in the correct Trash Bin. Either play 1 Trash Card or play any number of gems for special actions!&amp;#10;     It's Garbage Day! - Here's the catch - Only 6 Trash Cards fit in a Bin then it's full! Also you must play the cards in a number sequence only! Gems, however, give you special powers to strategise and win!&amp;#10;     Let's Talk Trash! - If a player puts trash in the wrong bin, you can challenge them. The loser must wear the Raccoon Hat! Best to refer to the Trash Table Card to learn Trash Item goes in which Bin.&amp;#10;     Lowest Score, Wins! - Once all the bins are full and no players can play any gems, the game ends! Add all the Trash Cards left with you, this is your score. Player with the lowest score, wins! &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
